[It is remarkable that the Russian Federation has been able to
provide statistics for 1997 already in January 1998. Notable changes
from 1996 are:
10 Diphtheria: progress in reducing incidence
11 Whooping cough (pertussis): doubling in incidence
21 Hemorrhagic fever with renal syndrome: 5-fold increase
22 Hepatitis A: marked reduction
24 Mumps: marked increase in both children & adults
30 Influenza: doubling of cases
32 HIV infection: almost double the number of cases compared to 1996
Perhaps one of our Russian subscribers can tell us if the reductions
in diphtheria and hepatitis A incidence are due to resumption of vaccination?
- Mod.JW
